# ğŸ”® Project Mirage
### The AI-Powered "Stunt Double" for Your API

**Project Mirage** turns a single JSON example into a fully functional, dynamic mock server in seconds. It uses Generative AI (Gemini) to write Python code that mimics your API's structure, data types, and logicâ€”so you can build your frontend before the backend is even ready.
---

## ğŸš€ Why use this?
Waiting for backend teams to finish APIs blocks frontend development. Static JSON files are boring and don't test edge cases.

**Mirage solves this:**
1.  **Give it a sample JSON.** (e.g., a User profile)
2.  **It writes a server.** (A real Python Flask app that generates random, valid data matching your schema)
3.  **It tests your resilience.** (Toggle **Chaos Mode** to randomly inject HTTP 500 errors)

## âœ¨ Features
-   **Zero-Config Mocking**: Just paste JSON, get a running API.
-   **Smart Data Generation**: Understood dates, enums, IDs, and relationships automatically.
-   **Cyberpunk UI**: A beautiful, glassmorphism-styled dashboard to control your mock.
-   **ğŸ”¥ Chaos Mode**: A toggle switch to simulate server crashes and verify your app's error handling.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
-   Python 3.x
-   A Google Gemini API Key ([Get one here](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey))

### 1. Clone & Install
```powershell
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/project-mirage.git
cd project-mirage
python -m venv .venv; .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install flask google-generativeai
```

### 2. Run the Engine
```powershell
python mirage_gemini.py
```

### 3. Create Your Mirage
1.  Open **`http://localhost:5000`** in your browser.
2.  Paste your **Gemini API Key**.
3.  Paste a **JSON sample** of the response you want.
4.  Click **INITIALIZE SHADOW NODE**.

ğŸ‰ **Done!** Your mock API is now live at `http://localhost:5000/api/mirage`.

---

## ğŸ§  How it Works

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[User Input JSON] -->|Sent to| B(Gemini AI)
    B -->|Generates| C[Python Logic]
    C -->|Injected into| D[Flask Server]
    D -->|Serves| E[Dynamic API Endpoint]
    F[Chaos Toggle] -->|Controls| D
```

1.  **Input**: You provide the "ideal" response.
2.  **Synthesis**: The AI analyzes the types (is "2023-01-01" a string or a date? is "status" an enum?) and writes a Python function to generate infinite variations of it.
3.  **Deployment**: This function is hot-loaded into the running Flask server.
4.  **Chaos**: When enabled, the server intercepts requests and randomly throws 500 errors.

---

## ğŸ“‚ Project Structure
-   `mirage_gemini.py`: The main application (UI + Server + AI Logic).
-   `gemini_shadow_server.py`: (Generated) The standalone server code produced by the tool.

## ğŸ›¡ï¸ Security Note
This tool executes AI-generated code locally. Always inspect the generated logic if you are working with sensitive environments. **Do not expose this server publicly without adding authentication.**

